Most Helpful First | Newest First 409 of 411 people found the following review helpful 5.0 out of 5 stars Plusses and Minuses, July 18, 2005 By Elaine Corwin "buttercupp21" (Concord, PA United States) - See all my reviews(REAL NAME) Amazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Cuisinart DCC-1200 Brew Central 12-Cup Programmable Coffeemaker, Black/Brushed Metal (Kitchen) I've had the Cuisinart DCC-1200 for about a week now. I was hesitant to spend so much on a coffee maker but I'm happy to report it's well worth it. Sure, you can get other brands of coffee makers for under $25 if economy is the most important feature, but I've had those machines and I decided that, this time, a good cup of coffee was most important for me. This unit makes the best coffee I've had in a home or office machine and better than most coffee I've had in restaurants.This coffee tastes smooooooth! I suspect the charcoal water filter is the reason for that. I also like the "shower head" design of the water spout. The water actually runs up a track onto the underside of the lid and is sprinkled over the ground coffee like a rain shower.It's an attractive unit but it also looks like a serious coffee maker. This unit is no toy. It looks and feels solid. The carafe has a good solid feel and balance. The plastic parts (like the plastic carafe lid and handle) feel like good heavyweight plastic and are well molded. It's not the lightweight crappy plastic that cracks and discolors easily in the cheap coffee makers.I like the 5 beeps when the coffee is ready. Now I can leave the kitchen and go clean or whatever and I don't have to keep running back to see if I can get a cup yet. I can hear the beeps. But if I really can't wait and want a cup in mid-brew, I can just remove the pot and pour a cup - you've got a full 30 seconds to reinsert the pot, before you risk an overflowing filter.I like the permanent gold-tone filter too. I always thought paper filters were a pain. They'd fold over sometimes and there'd be grounds in my coffee. But you can use paper filters in this machine if you want to. I just prefer the convenience of the gold-tone filter (top rack machine washable too).It has an indicator light for cleaning -- it says it's "self-cleaning" but really it's just a light telling you when you need to pour in a pot of water/vinegar and run it through to decalcify the unit. (I never thought to do that with my other units. Probably another reason my coffee wasn't as good as I wanted it to be.)The low-medium-high setting on the hot plate is pretty nice too. And the auto-shutoff feature is great. I don't have to worry about forgetting to turn the machine off.The instruction booklet is very good and very thorough. Comes with a parts reordering form too.What don't I like about this machine? It requires maintenance in that you have to change the charcoal filters. But actually I don't mind since I think they are the reason the coffee tastes so smooth, and they are very easy to change and not expensive [...]Also, the area in the top of the machine where you pour in the water is narrow but again this is just a minor inconvenience. Just have to pour a little carefully.So really it's almost all positives with a couple of very minor negatives. I highly recommend this coffee maker. Yes No Report abuse | PermalinkComment Comments (7)656 of 669 people found the following review helpful 4.0 out of 5 stars Fantastic coffeemaker - if you have the space, September 24, 2005 By Debbie Lee Wesselmann (the Lehigh Valley, PA) - See all my reviews(VINE VOICE) (2008 HOLIDAY TEAM) (TOP 50 REVIEWER) (REAL NAME) When my Braun FlavorSelect coffee maker unexpectedly stopped working, I had to scramble to find a new machine. I wanted another Braun, but unfortunately, they seem to have stopped making a 12 cup coffee maker. So I had to begin an intense search for a machine that had the features I wanted combined with good value. I finally found it with this Cuisinart model.The advantages? For one, it makes excellent and HOT coffee. The carafe is solidly constructed and fits securely in square body so there's no chance of someone accidentally knocking it loose. Because the lid fits tightly, the pour is precisely narrow and smooth, with no side leaks even when the pot is full. The basket fits inside the housing instead of swinging free like so many models which prevents a misalignment between the water and the filter; the conical (Krups/Braun style) basket accepts both paper filters and gold-tone, although I learned the hard way that not all gold filters fit. The timer is very easy to program, as is the clock. The carafe warmer can be set at low, medium, or high for the temperature that's right for you. I found the "high" setting too hot since I drink my coffee black (I like my coffee hot but not scalding!), but those who add a lot of milk might appreciate it. The brewing is quick and efficient, with the process taking about a minute a cup, maybe less. The retro/stainless look complements most modern kitchen d¨¦cors. There's a 1-4 cup setting to make sure such small amounts stay hot, and you can select how long the warmer remains on. The pot beeps five times when brewing is complete and just before the warming plate shuts off. Parts are top rack dishwasher safe. It comes with a water filter system designed to improve the taste of the brew.But the Cuisinart does have disadvantages. The water reservoir is located on the right side, in the back, which makes it a little challenging for lefties like me to dump the final bit of water inside even though the carafe pours very accurately. Although I haven't yet missed the opening, I do struggle briefly with those last few drops unless I use my right hand. The housing is fairly tall, so if your counter space is only under the cabinets, you may not be able to lift the top in its entirety. (This is when the small rear reservoir becomes a major issue as you have to have room to completely lift the rather large top toward the back.) Clearance required: 7.5" wide by 8.5" deep of counter space with no overhead obstruction to pull out for filling OR 21.5" of overhead space to fully lift top. Without the top open, the coffee maker measures 7.5"w x 8.5"d x 14.25"h.If you have the space for this coffee maker, you'll love it. I can't attest to how long it will last, but, as it comes with a three year warranty, I'm hoping for a good run. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? Yes No Report abuse | PermalinkComment Comments (14)723 of 746 people found the following review helpful 5.0 out of 5 stars Cuisinart DCC-1200 easily trumps Krups 180-46 Aroma Control, December 1, 2001 By Pawel Fludzinski - See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Cuisinart DCC-1200 Brew Central 12-Cup Programmable Coffeemaker, Black/Brushed Metal (Kitchen) Two weeks ago, I needed a new coffee maker. The Krups Aroma Control maker is in all the stores and catalogs, so I bought one in the local mall BEFORE reading the Amazon reviews. BIG MISTAKE. Lesson learned - read the reviews - many negative comments. I used it for 3 days, and readily understood the description (...) of "eye candy" (looks nice, but seems like cheap plastic) and weak coffee (what they describe as a feature - allowing the coffee to steep - is really a euphemism for a poorly designed system that is guaranteed to give you a weak cup of coffee). One redeeming feature - the carafe is very nice.Within 2 days of having the Krups, i was on Amazon looking for a replacement coffee maker (a good cup of coffee is critical in the morning!). I went out on the risk curve and ordered the new Cuisinart - no reviews yet. The Cuisinart has a more classic brewing system (water goes through grinds via gravity), yields a delicious cup of HOT coffee, has a variable temperature hot place, and looks and feels solid. We happen to have stainless steel appliances (refrigerator, freezer, stove), and it matches beautifully. Best news - excellent coffee!. I would highly recommend the Cuisinart. The problems are fixed on the current models., November 21, 2002 By BEN (CHARLOTTE, NC United States) - See all my reviewsThis review is from: Cuisinart DCC-1200 Brew Central 12-Cup Programmable Coffeemaker, Black/Brushed Metal (Kitchen) Folks, this is one excellent coffee maker. I read the comments here and decided to get it even though some had complained of spillage when lifting the lid and also the coffee not being hot enough. Well I can tell you that when I lift the lid on mine, the water rolls to the back and then drips back into the machine on a nifty little lip attached to the back of the machine. It appears that Cuisinart has engineered a solution for the complaints of spilled water that some reviewers mention. Also, the coffee coming out of the carafe of my machine has steam drifting off of it, so it is plenty hot, another complaint that seems to have been remedied. There were also a couple of complaints about finger prints on the stainless and the small LED clock being hard to read, but let's be for real, all brushed stainless appliances will fingerprint and this is a very stylish coffee maker, not a kitchen clock(that's what your microwave is for! (wink)). Actually I think the Cuisinart guys intended the clock for autoprogramming functions and made it LED to match the stainless on the machine. And if you don't like the water filter, you don't have to use it. It is a nicety and can be readily found if you search the net for "dcc1200 water filter".Enough defending complaints though. This machine makes superb coffee. It has the best carafe I have ever used(it will not spill a drop and it has a built-in plastic rim to keep you from busting it on the sink). It comes with a gold metal filter. Buy it and you will like it. And if for some strange reason you don't, then take it back. All jabs aside, this is an outstanding machine in form as well as function, and the people at Cuisinart obviously care what their customers think of their products. That means alot to me. How about you??? Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? Yes No Report abuse | PermalinkComment Comment (1)68 of 68 people found the following review helpful 5.0 out of 5 stars Best Coffeemaker that I have ever owned..Hands Down, September 3, 2003 By A CustomerThis review is from: Cuisinart DCC-1200 Brew Central 12-Cup Programmable Coffeemaker, Black/Brushed Metal (Kitchen) The Cuisinart DCC 1200 Brew Central Coffeemaker is the best coffeemaker that I have ever owned. I have been using it for the last several months and have not regreted making this purchase. I looked at other manufacturers of coffeemakers, Braun, Krups, and the like, but I felt that they didn't offer what this coffeemaker has to offer. I love the retro style with the stainless steel look. It's a breeze to program and if you don't need 12 cups a coffee, you press one button on the front and you can make a great small pot of coffee. It by far makes the best pot of coffee that I have ever tasted, and since I roast my own coffee at home I should know.There are a couple of minor issues, but they are so minor it isn't a large drawback to the machine. It can be a chore to pour in the water and with it large size, with top lid open, you have to pull it out from under the upper kitchen cabinets to fill. It's a minor inconvenience, but when you use it daily you slowly find little tricks that make those minor issues seem to disappear. Others have complained about not seeing the clock very well, but why depend on your coffeemaker to tell time when it is really there to be programmed to wake up to a hot pot of delicious coffee. The condensation issue hasn't been a problem for me, so I can't comment on that issue that some have had with this coffeemaker.I will say that if you are looking for a great coffemaker, then this is the one for you. It's a bit more money than most coffeemakers, but I think that for the money this coffeemaker is the best bang for the buck and you will never regret owning one. Perskie "ceruleana" (New York, NY USA) - See all my reviews(VINE VOICE) (TOP 1000 REVIEWER) (HALL OF FAME REVIEWER) (REAL NAME) Amazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Cuisinart DCC-1200 Brew Central 12-Cup Programmable Coffeemaker, Black/Brushed Metal (Kitchen) I recently decided that it was time to buy a new coffeemaker and wanted the BEST! I did my research thoroughly, online and by word-of-mouth, and decided on Cuisinart's DCC-1200 12-Cup Brew Central Coffeemaker. This terrific gadget arrived a week ago and I am thrilled with it.I love my coffee and usually make time to have at least one, if not two, 12 oz. mugs of freshly brewed java before I leave the house in the AM. Although this is a 12 cup coffeemaker, the settings are geared for a 5 oz. cup. So, for those of you who think a 12 cup machine is too much, this factor should be considered. Coffee is 98% water and if the quality of water used is not good, your final result won't be either. Cuisinart's DCC-1200 has a charcoal water filter that removes chlorine, calcium, bad tastes and odors. The self-cleaning feature is terrific and a warning light will flash to notify when calcium buildup is interfering with the machine's functioning mechanism. Programming for delayed brew time is a snap with the LCD digital clock. One of the features I like best is the heater plate control knob. I like my coffee steaming hot - and this feature assures that I can control the temperature of the nonstick heating plate. The machine also looks great on my kitchen counter.I had thought about buying a combination coffeemaker/coffee grinder and decided against it. Apparently, many combination machines leave a sludgy residue and are a hassle to clean. I preferred using my own grinder, which is easy to clean, and this coffee maker - also very easy to clean and maintain. This machine is a coffee lover's dream!!I bought the BEST! Very highly recommended!!JANA Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? Yes No Report abuse | PermalinkComment Comment61 of 62 people found the following review helpful 4.0 out of 5 stars Different breed of cat, January 8, 2003 By BURGESS WILLIAMS (UKIAH, CA United States) - See all my reviewsThis review is from: Cuisinart DCC-1200 Brew Central 12-Cup Programmable Coffeemaker, Black/Brushed Metal (Kitchen) Just brewed my 1st cup of coffee with the Brew Central DCC-1200.Before my purchase through Amazon I read all 58 reviews of this product and was concerned about the 50-50 division of opinion on the quality of the brew, whether it was hot enough (I need it hot), and the water mess on the counter when the cover was raised. I should add that I recently purchased and returned a Krups (great coffee but a clunker for endurance--froze up twice after a few months operation) and Capresso (dull, undrinkable coffee).My empiracle assessment of the DCC-1200 is that:1. The brew is superior;2. It is hot--can't see how it could be hotter;3. A plastic lip connected to the reservoir cover on the back of the machine catches any condensation runoff when the cover is raised. Yes No Report abuse | PermalinkComment Comment506 of 561 people found the following review helpful 5.0 out of 5 stars Brew Central DCC-1200, Good, Hot Coffee, March 12, 2004 By Scott D. Gibson (New York) - See all my reviews(REAL NAME) This review is from: Cuisinart DCC-1200 Brew Central 12-Cup Programmable Coffeemaker, Black/Brushed Metal (Kitchen) First I'd like to say that these review sites really kill me. Invariably, you have to wade through countless trivial comments like, "I had to turn the spool wheel too many times before I could change the string on my string trimmer" or, here's a classic, "the stereo I bought is just too loud and I have to keep the volume at the number 5 setting all the time." (trust me, this is from an actual review). Well, you'll be happy to know that the reviews for the DCC-1200 are no different. Anywhere from "why do you have to turn the knob to brew and then flick a switch for on" to, "I can hear the plastic creaking as it heats up" (that one really makes me laugh) to, "it's just too tall and doesn't fit under my cabinets" (didn't you size it up before you bought it)?Look people, this unit makes coffee. It does it well and it does it like it's supposed to. You pour water in the top, add your favorite beans, wait a bit and, here's the kicker, coffee comes out the bottom! Holy smokes! It's got two knobs, an on and off switch and a few buttons to set things like the clock. To brew, turn the knob to brew and flick the on switch. To auto-brew, turn the knob to auto-brew and flick the on switch. To program the clock/auto on/auto off, turn the knob to clock/auto on/auto off and... press a button. Wow, this is really tough stuff. And, to make matters worse, omygosh, the LCD clock doesn't have a back light!! Armageddon here we come. You don't have enough clocks in your kitchen between the wall, the microwave, the oven, and every other stinking thing that has to tell you the time these days? The other knob adjusts the hot plate setting. Low-Med-High. Trust me, there are many complaints that the Cuisinart doesn't get their coffee hot enough. Not hot enough? How hot do you really want it? I'm sure Cuisinart wasn't thinking about their specs reaching boiling temperature when they designed this thing. Trust me folks, it's close enough. I'd say close to McDonald's scalding hot coffee but I won't even sue Cuisinart for potentially burning my crotch. As for the plastic creaking, when the temperature heats up, the plastic expands inside, what do you want anyway? Whatddya mean it's only stainless steel on the outside? I've been ripped off!!! I mean come on, if you really want a true stainless steel coffee maker, go spend the $2000 and buy professional so that you can mount it on the dash of your Beemer. Just don't waste our time with comments like this. Oh yeah and the alarm/beeping that everyone's complaining about? Well, let me just say that the "Hounds of the Baskervilles" comment is a little unjustified. I would hate to hear what this person does when their microwave goes off, or, if their telephone rings, or if one of the kids makes a noise. Folks, this is a series of 5 small beeps when the brewing cycle is near completion. Kind of a tee tee tee tee tee. So, unless you sleep with your coffee maker on your night stand, I wouldn't worry so much about this one. Condensation. I don't know one coffee maker out there that when you open the lid to dump your grounds just after the brewing is complete where some of it doesn't drip on the countertop. So, suck it up. Get your sink sponge and wipe it up. Are we that inconvenienced by this?And finally, the dreaded reservoir comment. "It's too small and I pour water all over the place." Blah blah. Pour water in, get coffee out. So far, I haven't missed the bullseye. Could I be doing something wrong here? And about those darned tank markers. Does anybody honestly use those things? Fill up the pot and pour it in. Now you know how much coffee you'll make. Huh?!The bottom line is that this is a good coffee maker. It has a self cleaning cycle to tell you when to decalcify, makes piping hot coffee but... oh no, produces condensation. It's kind of like when you heat water on the stove and it produces that steamy stuff, and it forms those... water droplets. Ah whatever. Look, if you're the type who doesn't have to have their maid do everything for them or worse flog the person who doesn't quite fold the towel right on the towel bar, go out and buy this product, you won't be disappointed. Yes No Report abuse | PermalinkComment Comments (55)701 of 781 people found the following review helpful 2.0 out of 5 stars Design Flaws Aplenty, July 2, 2007 By Michael Z. Jody "Psychoanalyst, amateur music... (NYC & East Hampton, NY United States) - See all my reviews(REAL NAME) This review is from: Cuisinart DCC-1200BW Brew Central 12-Cup Programmable Coffeemaker, Matte Black Metal (Kitchen) OK, I admit it, I bought this machine because I thought it looked terrific, cool design, heavy duty manufacture, and I was fond of the retro-chic of the dials and switches, like an airplane dashboard from thirty years ago. The machine, however, has several design flaws that have greatly mitigated my warm feelings.For one thing, the water reservoir into which you pour the water is located in the very back of the machine, next to the hinge for the lid. It is awkward to use, the opening is too small, and your water often either splashes out of the back or into the coffee grounds.Second, the hot water comes out of the lid and onto the grounds, but when closed, the lid is too close to the grounds and gets a lot of backsplash. The grounds end up adhered to the lid which must be wiped off every time you use it or it will clog. But when you wipe it actually pushes the grounds into the spray head. Also, if you fill the (too small) gold filter while it is seated in the machine you are very likely to get grounds into the water reservoir which then necessitates a difficult cleaning of the entire works. And I suspect that even if you fill it and then place it in the machine, the grounds sometimes get splashed into the reservoir during the brewing process.The gold filter that fits this machine is too small. We like our coffee strong and if you put in enough coffee for a whole 12 cup pot, it expands into the works and again clogs everything making you have to clean it.Lastly, within about two weeks of our purchasing the machine, the little thingy at the bottom of the filter holder fell out (it is held in by a rubber band) and now we can no longer pull the pot out in the middle of the brew cycle (a convenient feature for those of us who are impatient and/or in a hurry) but must wait until the whole pot is made to get that first cup.In sum, a beautiful and indeed heavy duty machine, but quite flawed. I liked our old Braun maker much better. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? Yes No Report abuse | PermalinkComment Comments (127)? column7: Customer Reviews Trevi Blue King Comforter Set 1 Review 5 star: (0)4 star: (0)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (1) Average Customer Review 1.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 1.0 out of 5 stars Picture is Misleading, September 5, 2012 By nnmhj - See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Trevi Blue King Comforter Set I ordered this set for my bedroom, thinking that it was white and blue. BUT it is very very ivory--very much yellow-cream. If you're looking for ivory and blue it would be very nice, but if you're going off the picture and think it's white and blue, you will be very disapointed. Also, make suer you read what it comes with because it is only the bedskirt, comforter and two shams. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? This review is from: King Micro Fleece Blanket with Satin Binding Sage Green It's hard to find a good old fashioned blanket today. A good wool blanket nearly costs more than the bed. I do like satin on blankets though, and that is hard to find. Although I'm not crazy about the 'micro-fleece' blankets as they seem to tear and fall apart quickly, this on seems so soft and it is very warm. I was surprised that the satin goes all the way around the blanket and not just at the top and bottom. So far, I love this blanket and may just get a couple more! column7: Customer Reviews King Coaster Bookcase Storage Bed in Rich Cappuccino Finish 1 Review 5 star: (1)4 star: (0)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 5.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 9 of 9 people found the following review helpful 5.0 out of 5 stars LOVE IT!, January 27, 2012 By JLS (South Florida) - See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: King Coaster Bookcase Storage Bed in Rich Cappuccino Finish (Kitchen) This bed has solved our storage problems. We have a smallish bedroom and decided to down-grade the furniture to just a bed and tv unit but of course still needed drawers. All 8 drawers are deep and provide plenty of room plus the two smaller drawers in the head board are a bonus. I thought I would miss having a bedside table but I can easily reach behind me to the shelf above my head. There are two open holes in the corners of the shelves for cords and the top of the head board can also be used as a shelf.It arrived on a pallet in three heavy boxes but my husband and I were able to get it unpacked and built in under three hours. One of the drawers came off it's tracks during shipping because a board (used to stop the drawer from going too far into the base) had come out. We just nailed it back in place and put the drawer back, pretty impressed that was the only hiccup during shipping.The wood is of quality and the finish has a rich look. All and all I just love this bed. It was worth the price compared to other storage beds. The furniture stores always charge you extra for each piece you add on so we feel like we got a bargain....plus you don't have to dust under the bed anymore! This review is from: Black and White Zebra Print Fauxfur 7-piece Comforter Set - KING Its a good concept, but the comforter overall looked terrible. the picture looks beautiful, but I was completely let down.The "faux fur" isn't what you'd expect; it is made from the same material those Dollar Store stuffed animals are made from. I expect the design to wash off in the first wash. The black bordering is made from the same material as a wind breaker, and it is very uncomfortable. The pillows are very cheaply made, there was no neck roll pillow, and the shams are WAY too big, they are twice the size of my large pillows. column7: Customer Reviews 12" King 5 Lb Memory Foam Mattress W/5" Visco with / New Improved Dual Air Flow System. Compares to the Rhapsody 1 Review 5 star: (1)4 star: (0)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 5.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 1 of 1 people found the following review helpful 5.0 out of 5 stars King-5"/5lb memory foam mattress, February 22, 2012 By F. Spyropoulos - See all my reviews(REAL NAME) Amazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: 12" King 5 Lb Memory Foam Mattress W/5" Visco with / New Improved Dual Air Flow System. Compares to the Rhapsody Just ordered and received mattress in 3 days, I don't have prime. That's a petty fast delivery and it was free!Since I just got the bed, I'm only going to touch on a few things. I will update the review in a few months, to let you know how it sleeps.For starters, its crazy how they fit a king sized bed into a box about 15" x 6 feet! I layed it down in a spare room and opened the box. Inside was a squished rolled up pancake. It's tightly wrapped with two strong layers of thick plastic and taped on a cylindrical shape. Once you cut open the plastic it regains it's shape almost immediately. Within a half hour or so it was exactly 12" thick and exactly the standard measurements of a king mattress.The cover on this thing is great. Soft, thick and stretchy. Feels and looks like very nice quality material. I have read lots of other reviews about memory foam smelling and was expecting the worst. This mattress had absolutely no smell, well of course there is that "new smell" smell. Maybe since this is USA made, it has less chemicals?? Whatever the case may be, there was only a smell when you bury your face into it. By the next day I could barely smell anything, even with my nose pushed into it.As far as the "feel" of the bed, it is awesome. I just couldn't help but jump into this thing and test it out right after it fluffed up! It's obviously hard-ish at first, as are all memory foam beds. Within 5 seconds you sink into its luxurious foam embrace. Can't say if it's hard or soft....it's memory foam, you sink in...how do you judge firmness? I'm 180 pound male and I sink in just the right amount. It actually feels like my back is stretching back to normal. I work construction and the main reason I wanted a memory foam bed was to help my back feel better. On my old spring mattress every morning was filled with lower back pain, kinks in my neck and shoulders. So when I layed on this new memory foam bed, it immediately felt like it was aligning my spine!So for now this is all I can say about this mattress, just wanted to point out a few basic things before I come back and write an update. It its the exact size it should be in every dimension. It had almost zero smell, if the "new smell" bothers you then don'tbuy a new car or anything new for that matter! I did take off the cover to check inside and it's glued together right and cut perfectly and you can see the dual airflow cut into it.So far so good! I'll keep you guys posted in the coming months. But as for now this bed is exactly as advertised and very highquality, at this price its a steal. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? This review is from: United Linens Sabrina 300 Thread Count 100-Percent Cotton 4-Piece Paisley Embroidery Sheet Set, Queen, Sage (Misc.) This set goes perfect with my Nastalgia "Leigh" bed spread. The Embroidery somewhat matches the quilt and the flowers are identical except for color of course. However, I did have to exchange it since the embroidery stitching was unravelling and it wasn't sewn straight. Thank you Amazon for paying the return shipping. Watch out for all those loose threads. I was disappointed that it lost its' sheen after washing and drying it. Overall the cloth (300 thread count) is solid and a good thickness. I would recommend this item. column7: Customer Reviews S. Lichtenberg Co. Brilliance 100-Percent Polyester, King 7-Piece Comforter Set, Purple 1 Review 5 star: (0)4 star: (1)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 4.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice but not cat compatible, April 23, 2012 By E. Skluzacek "ejskluz" (Minneapolis, MN) - See all my reviews(REAL NAME) This review is from: S. Lichtenberg Co. Brilliance 100-Percent Polyester, King 7-Piece Comforter Set, Purple (Kitchen) First a note on color: the overall color is a lot darker than in the photo but unless your monitor has been color calibrated with the manufacturer's, NEVER expect to get the same color as the picture. The skirt and background look almost brown in the soft, low light in my bedroom. Having said all that, the color is exactly what I wanted, sort of aubergine and not pink at all. The pattern isn't printed, it's woven, sort of like embroidery, which is unfortunately not at all compatible with cat claws. Then again, if you have cats, you probably already know that you shouldn't expect your nice things to stay nice. On the bright side, the cat hair doesn't show at all. On the dark side, the snags are so extensive that the whole thing looks kind of furry. The good news is, now that it's already ruined, I decided to go ahead and try machine washing it even though it's supposed to be dry clean only and it came out just fine, just a tiny bit lumpy along the edges. So now I have a perfectly worn in, lovely aubergine bedspread that I can machine wash - I'm quite happy with that and would probably buy this again if I ever decide the "worn in" look has crossed over to "worn out". McKinney - See all my reviews(REAL NAME) This review is from: Christopher Adams 1600 Thread Count California King Size Sheet Set in Latte Cream I purchased these same sheets from a mall vendor. When I got home, I realized I'd been taken. The 1600TC text on the label is simply a model number--don't be fooled into thinking this is 1600 thread count. These sheets are thin and made of some kind of polyester material. I also realized when I got home that wording I thought I saw on the label that said "Egyptian Cotton" actually said "Egyptian Comfort." An obvious attempt to mislead consumers. Avoid these low-quality sheets. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? This review is from: Veratex, Tarlow King Comforter set (Kitchen) I looked at this comforter set for a few months before I purchased it. The quality of the comforter is okay. The top is made of a heavy material and looks nice but has a rough feel. The comforter is somewhat heavy and can get hot. Also, the layers of the comforter are not "attached" so there tends to be air pockets which cause the comforter to not always lay flat. The bedskirt is somewhat thin but a nice sea foam color. It is also dry clean only so there is probably no chance of the comforter becoming softer over time. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? column7: Customer Reviews Set of 2 - Beverly Hills Polo Club - 95% Feather - 5% Down Pillow 400tc - Filled & Finished in USA - 3 Year Warranty - King 1 Review 5 star: (0)4 star: (0)3 star: (0)2 star: (1)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 2.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 2.0 out of 5 stars stinky pillow with a polyester cover, August 24, 2012 By optimistic pessimist - See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Set of 2 - Beverly Hills Polo Club - 95% Feather - 5% Down Pillow 400tc - Filled & Finished in USA - 3 Year Warranty - Queen I am a bit annoyed about this product. You will notice that the description claims to be odor free. This is not so, upon arrival they smelled like wet chicken. Imagine the smell of a wet dog, but with feathers. These pillows are also advertised to be 400tc. I foolishly thought that would mean cotton, but the description didn't say what type of fabric. Sadly, it is very thin 100% polyester. I put these pillows in the dryer to fluff them up and knock down the smell a bit. They came out of the dryer with feathers sticking out everywhere, but thankfully less odor. I won't be testing these out till I can find sturdy covers for them and make sure they have aired out sufficiently. Lesson learned. I should have taken the time to actually go shopping, instead of using the internet. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? column7: Customer Reviews Tribeca Living 450 Thread Count Egyptian Cotton Percale King Deep Pocket Sheet Set, Bone 1 Review 5 star: (0)4 star: (0)3 star: (1)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 3.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 3.0 out of 5 stars Good Sheets but...., September 1, 2012 By Frani (California) - See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Tribeca Living 450 Thread Count Egyptian Cotton Percale King Deep Pocket Sheet Set, Bone (Misc.) I like the weight of these sheets, the 450 thread count, the one-inch wide elastic on the fitted sheet that just pulls the sheet perfectly around the mattress. I like the that these sheets are percale and do feel cool and crisp. But I don't like how the sheets are wrinkled after laundering. I've washed these about 5 time now and the sheets are definitely softer but the wrinkles are still there...I truly hate ironing and I especially don't feel like ironing sheets. I'm hoping that with a few more (or dozen) washes, I won't even notice the wrinkles...a girl can only hope :) I would give this sheet set 3.5 stars. column7: Customer Reviews 7Pcs King Sydney Bedding Bed in a Bag Comforter Set 1 Review 5 star: (0)4 star: (1)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 4.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 3 of 3 people found the following review helpful 4.0 out of 5 stars 7Pcs King Sydney Bed in a Bag from KingLinen, August 3, 2011 By CT (Las Vegas, NV) - See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: 7Pcs King Sydney Bedding Bed in a Bag Comforter Set Bottom line - very nice set, very rich looking, and at a great price. The only reason I didn't give it 5 stars is because there are a few loose threads here and there that make me a little nervous, and I want to see how it will perform over time. It is beautiful and soft, and definitely not thick and heavy weight-wise. It is MUCH darker than it looks in the pic. This wasn't a problem for me, but if you're buying it because of the particular shade you think it is based on the pic...think again. The fabric is very metallic/shiny and therefore needs to be ironed before you use it, and, I'm guessing, at regular intervals; since it is so reflective, the wrinkles really show. It's not as generously cut width-wise as it could be - the sides are shorter than my last comforter. If you have generously cut sheets like I do, it just covers the sheet. But, with free shipping and at this price point, I'm very happy with it so far! I'll post an update as I see how it wears. Total luxury!, July 1, 2011 By Ashley (Maryland) - See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Peacock Alley LCA-OQSET PEW Luxury Linens Luca 100-Percent Egyptian Cotton Queen Duvet Set, Pewter (Misc.) I just received this queen duvet set in pewter, and I love it. I've never had a more luxurious duvet cover. The fabric is super-soft and lightweight. I figured the pattern would be printed, but it's actually woven in! The color looks slightly darker in person (on my monitor, the pewter looks like a very light taupe with white flowers but in person it is more a light/medium taupe with cream flowers), which was fine with me. I just pulled it out of the package and stuck it on my duvet without washing it or anything. It doesn't smell and there aren't really even very noticable the out-of-the-package wrinkles. The only downside is that I ordered a queen size set and it comes with standard shams. I actually have slightly larger pillows (king/queen) on my bed, so I'll have to switch to smaller pillows. Overall, though, this duvet looks and feels like something you'd see in a 5 star hotel! I'm very pleased. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? column7: Customer Reviews 10-PC Taupe & Black California King size Hotel Down Alternative Bed in a bag Comforter set including a Duvet set+ sheet set+ down alternative comforter By sheetsnthings 1 Review 5 star: (0)4 star: (0)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (1) Average Customer Review 1.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 2 of 2 people found the following review helpful 1.0 out of 5 stars Craptastic!, May 11, 2011 By starvingstudent - See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: 10-PC Taupe & Black California King size Hotel Down Alternative Bed in a bag Comforter set including a Duvet set+ sheet set+ down alternative comforter By sheetsnthings My wife and I needed a comforter for our cali-king sized bed, and we didn't want to spend a horrendous amount of money on one so we thought to look on Amazon. We thought we found the perfect-looking set for the right size. The picture looked nothing like what we got, and supposedly what we ordered was the only version we could get (I understand that sometimes comforters don't always display the exact color scheme/pattern when multiple variations of the same theme are available). We were greatly disappointed to open our comforter set and discover a hideous black-and-brown monstrosity, instead of the black, brown and white pattern shown in the item image. We are currently in the process of trying to return the set and get our money back. We will just have to shop elsewhere to make sure we get what we want. column7: Customer Reviews King's Brand E008 TV Stand Entertainment Center with Storage, Chocolate Finish 1 Review 5 star: (1)4 star: (0)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 5.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 1 of 1 people found the following review helpful 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful Product and Easy to Assemble, April 3, 2012 By J. Price "Big Daddy" (High Point, NC) - See all my reviews(REAL NAME) Amazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: King's Brand E008 TV Stand Entertainment Center with Storage, Chocolate Finish (Misc.) My wife and I spent quite a bit of time looking for the perfect television stand. We wanted something that was not too expensive (so we could purchase two for symmetry)but did not look and feel like cheap pressed board. This product was a perfect choice.The look and feel is heavy, well crafted for the price and it's easy to assemble. If you follow instructions perfectly (one area: the instructions could be just a tad easier to follow but I am partially convinced that's more me than the instructions), you just snap and click and you'll have a beautiful furniture stand.Pros:--Solid design--Beautiful color--Easy to assembleCons--The easy to assemble design is snap based. Within each connection point are embedded snap assemblies. They tend to come out easy if you don't nail the instructions first time around (again folks, more user error than anything but just so you know)--There is no hole in the back for television cords. If you are just using this as a furniture stand as it's intended, that's fine. Although it says it's a television stand, strange there's no pre-drilled holes!Overall, I am still giving it 5 stars primarily because my cons are really related to MY challenges versus the product. No need in taking a star away from them when it's really a purchaser issue!I recommend the product. Great decorative stand or if, like me, you want to use for your receiver, you will just need to bore a small hole in the back for your cords. well worth it to not have to use a drill to put the darned thing together! Just follow the instructions FULLY! Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? column7: Customer Reviews Natori Empress 400-Thread-Count King Fitted Sheet 1 Review 5 star: (0)4 star: (0)3 star: (0)2 star: (1)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 2.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 5 of 5 people found the following review helpful 2.0 out of 5 stars Item is nice, but the photo is really misleading., July 18, 2009 By M. Su "More Dessert" (Los Angeles, CA USA) - See all my reviews(VINE VOICE) (REAL NAME) Amazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Natori Empress 400-Thread-Count Fitted Sheet (Kitchen) This is for the fitted sheet, which is the bottom item of the photo. The nice floral pattern on the silk finsh does NOT exist. Even the color, if you look closely, it's not the ivory color of the top 3 items, it's a more pinkish color.I admit, the color is written in the description and I didn't read it carefully enough. But that photo is just bad. Even has a 2nd photo showing the nice floral pattern on the sheet, making me believe that does exist. It may be hard to get an attractive picture on just the fitten sheet, but this photo has to be changed to be more clear of the item that is being sold.Don't mind paying $300 just for the fitten sheets, but at this price, it not only need to be comfortable, it needs to look nice as well. unfortunately without the floral patterns and the pink color, it feels and looks like just like a $50 set of 1200 thread sheets. This review is from: Luxurious DARK BLUE Damask Stripe, KING Size. EIGHT (8) Piece GOOSE DOWN Comforter BED IN A BAG Set. 1500 Thread Count Ultra Soft Single-Ply 100% Egyptian Cotton. INCLUDES 4pc BED SHEET Set, 3pc DUVET SET & GOOSE DOWN Comforter First, there is now way this is 1500 TC. Maybe 300 or 400. For the price, I would shop somewhere else. Cheap down comforter and a 300/400 TC sheet set is much cheaper purchased separately. Of course, returning these items is nearly impossible after sleeping in them. Of course, you can't get a good idea of quality until you sleep in them. I'd value this set at $100 for a good deal or $150 for standard price. $200 at absolute top end.The sheets do look nice and they are relatively soft. This review is from: Rayon from BAMBOO Sheet Set - King Blue 600 Thread Count Cotton Sheet Set Bamboo doesn't exactly evoke images of comfort and softness, but that's exactly what these sheets are. I personally find them more comfortable than their 100% cotton counterparts. I LOVE these sheets, and getting into bed is always a relaxing joy with them on. These sheets are well made and very sturdy, which makes me happy they will last a long time.I only even thought of looking for sheets made with bamboo fiber after knitting with yarn made from bamboo and being enthralled with its softness. It transfers well to sheets, too! Plus bamboo is an easily renewable resource due to quick growth, which adds a "being green" component to them.All in all, I'm absolutely satisfied with these sheets. column7: Customer Reviews Classic Brands Instant Foundation for Bed Mattress, King 1 Review 5 star: (0)4 star: (1)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 4.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 2 of 2 people found the following review helpful 4.0 out of 5 stars A competent wood foundation, October 2, 2011 By James Allman "traditional conservative" (Houston, Texas) - See all my reviews(REAL NAME) Amazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Classic Brands Instant Foundation for Bed Mattress, Queen (Misc.) I needed a foundation for an air bed I was putting together, and this foundation definitely fit the bill. The main frame of the foundation fit together easily with carriage bolts, while the slats (some 11 of them) had to be screwed in with wood screws - not difficult if you have an electric drill. While the assembly took longer than 5 minutes, it wasn't bad - it definitely took less than an hour. The case was very nice; from the outside, you can't tell that it's not a box spring foundation. Buyers should be aware that this foundation is relatively open, with roughly 4 inch gaps between 2 inch slats. This is no problem for light mattresses (air or spring), but heavier mattresses (foam or water) might distort on this foundation. People using those heavier mattresses may want to spend more money for a foundation with more slats. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? This review is from: Beverly Hills Polo Club Dobby Stripe 3-Piece Full/Queen Comforter Set, Black (Kitchen) I was completely surprised when I opened the package. The picture makes the comforter looks much, much better than it actually is. It just looks and feels like a poor quality comforter, something on the same level as a "bed in a bag" set. Also, there are these odd stitchings scattered throughout the comforter. You can see them if you take a REALLY close look at the picture. I'm not sure what they were going for with them. While they are certainly intentionally placed (they are arranged in regular distances from each other), they make the comforter look like it was restitched and like there were mistakes during its manufacturing.I've bought several items off Amazon before, and I've never written a negative review before. And this will be the first item I will be returning. I suggest you find something else. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? column7: Customer Reviews Banana Yellow - Comforter - King 1 Review 5 star: (0)4 star: (0)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (1) Average Customer Review 1.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 3 of 3 people found the following review helpful 1.0 out of 5 stars total Disappointment, May 21, 2012 By Alice Habbal (Monroe, NC USA) - See all my reviews(REAL NAME) Amazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Banana Yellow - Comforter - King This comforter purchase was a mistake! I should have sent it back to begin with. For $100, I got...a comforter...a CHEAPLY made comforter and that is it! No shams, no bed skirt, which I knew, but I expected better quality and was planning to order those items. Those would have been another $100. I do not mind paying for quality..this is NOT worth what I paid. It is hard to find bright yellow, so the color is not the issue. Good color. The quality is the issue. We have probably slept under this comforter less than 10 nights as it is in our "second" home. It is already bunching up inside and seams are shifting. I am so disappointed, I am just going to suck up my loss, donate it to Goodwill and make my own duvet cover and put a good quality stuffer in. Williams (Midwest City, Ok) - See all my reviews(REAL NAME) Amazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Francesca Quilt Set Size: King I fell in love with this design for the quilt, and it did not disappoint. The shams are a perfect fit for my king pillows, the quilt itself it great, if not a little longer than the quilts I am used to. Which, don't get me wrong, is great, just something I myself need to adapt to. The only thing is the stray threads, of which there are not a huge amount, just enough to be noticeable. Makes me worry slightly that it will eventually unravel. Also on the inside of the rings, where the white is, there is a place where it is pieced together, and that one spot looks a little tacky, but you have to look for it to see it, my husband has yet to notice, and it is on his side of the bed. All in all, a good buy. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? column7: Customer Reviews Belle Epoque 420-Thread Count Quilted King Sham, Champagne 1 Review 5 star: (0)4 star: (1)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 4.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 4.0 out of 5 stars Very satisfied with Quality and Style, July 7, 2012 By Susan G. (Warren County, NJ) - See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Belle Epoque 420-Thread Count Quilted King Sham, Lilac (Kitchen) I purchased these shams to match a Nautica summer quilt that I purchased on sale and it appeared that Nautica did not make matching King sized shams. The Lilac color looked very attractive with the purples, lilac, and blues of the quilt. The only question I have is why were the King shams sold and packaged as single shams and not a pair. I got confused and ordered what I thought was a pair of shams and then received the package with only one sham. Who buys a single King sham or pillowcase???? Once I got the other one, they looked lovely on my bed. These are a bit pricey, but the quality is excellent and I expect to enjoy them for a long time. Also, they are easy to wash and come out of the dryer looking great. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? column7: Customer Reviews 3 Pieces Black 100% Cotton Damask Stripe Reversible Duvet Cover with Shams Set King Size Bedding 1 Review 5 star: (0)4 star: (0)3 star: (1)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 3.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 3 of 3 people found the following review helpful 3.0 out of 5 stars You get what you pay for, January 1, 2011 By Julie "the garden girl" (Northwest US) - See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: 3 Pieces Black 100% Cotton Damask Stripe Reversible Duvet Cover with Shams Set King Size Bedding I purchased this set to go over a new comforter. I am not using the shams (I prefer pillow cases), just the comforter cover. The white lining fabric inside the shams did get a bit misplaced after washing, but still seemed functional. The shams don't have a zipper closure, just an opening in the back.The material is plain cotton, a little heavier than normal sheet weight. The material did wrinkle pretty badly after I washed it, but that's to expected with 100% cotton. My main issue with the material is that it shows dust and lint, but I guess since it's black that's also to be expected. I don't use dryer sheets, maybe that would make a difference.Be aware that unlike in the picture, the stripes go horizontally. This doesn't bother me. The pattern is pretty subtle anyway. I like the muted stripes, it goes with the various colored sheets we have.The cover closes with a zipper that seems a little lightweight but does the job. The zipper was actually difficult to find, and the comforter is completely enclosed inside of the cover. I would have preferred ties inside the corners to tie onto my comforter (which has loops for that purpose). However the comforter does seem to stay put without them.All in all, this is a decent product for the low price. I do not know how durable it will be since I have only had it a short time and washed it once. However the cover seems to work just fine and I don't have any real issues with it.**Update after 2 months of use** This cover picks up **every** bit of lint and hair, I wish it was made of some other type of material. It rubbed fuzzy material off of the duvet so that the entire inside of the cover had this white cottony fuzz on it. I washed it inside out. Big mistake. The seams are not finished in any way, just one straight line of stitching and raw cut material. Long threads pulled out of the raw edges and wrapped themselves tightly around the cover during the washing and drying. I ended up cutting out all the loose threads and sewed a zig zag stitch all along the inside seams, which took care of the problem. I also added loops to the inner corners.I actually like to sew so this wasn't a big deal, but it really irritated me. I mean, come on, how difficult would it be for the manufacturer to SERGE the seams? Really? The cover works and I don't have any more problems with it (as long as I vacuum it to pick up the lint), but you really do get what you pay for.Update on the pillow shams. They are cheap too. The fusible interfacing shredded after two washings and dryings. I guess they really mean it when the tag says to wash cold and dry on low. I would err on the side of caution and hang dry them. I ended up cutting out the interfacing altogether, but there is still a bit left I couldn't get out. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? column7: Customer Reviews Prodigy Adjustable Bed with Massage, Split King Set 1 Review 5 star: (1)4 star: (0)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 5.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 115 of 116 people found the following review helpful 5.0 out of 5 stars A Perfect Option for my bed, June 13, 2011 By Carl Franklin "Author and Professor" (Cedar City, UT USA) - See all my reviews(REAL NAME) This review is from: Adjustables Prodigy Adjustable Bed, Queen (Misc.) I actually ended up buying this frame with my bed from the local store; however, I was going to order here at Amazon (Amazon didn't have the mattresses I wanted and the local guy beat the price). I wanted to write this review simply because the frame has been a great purchase, no matter where you buy it. The price at Amazon is very good, too. Here's a few items worth mentioning about the bed. In all, these items add up to the value of the extra money you'll pay for this frame.My wife and I both have bad backs, mine from arthritis and her's from a failed back surgery. She spends a lot of time in bed because of her new disability (thanks Doc for your incompetence!). So finding a decent combination of mattress and adjustable frame was a must for us. We had looked at the Leggett & Platt frames at several stores, and new that the S-cape series had many features we wanted. This included adjustability of both leg and foot position along with the massage. To be honest, I hadn't planned to buy the massage originally, but now I'm glad we did.The L&P frame provided a little higher lifting level for the feet, something that was very important to my wife. Other frames, such as the Ergo and the frame for the Serta iComfort bed, didn't lift the legs as high.The massage feature seemed to be an extra I would not use much. That's where this Prodigy series begins to shine. I actually have used the massage more than I ever thought I would, but surprisingly it has been in the mornings. The ability of this frame to set the massage as an alarm is actually a big advantage, especially if you suffer from back pain or have tightness in the mornings. Most mornings I woke up very achy, and I knew that was in part because of the bed I was using. So buying a new mattress helped, but now getting up is assisted even more when there's a gentle massage along with the alarm. I set the massage to start a few minutes before I actually want to get up, and it slowly increases intensity over time. My guess is the massage starts the blood flowing a little earlier, and it helps to ease the tension generally caused by my joints being inactive over night. It is pretty amazing, though I won't say it is the answer to all my prayers as an arthritis sufferer. If you have arthritis then don't kid yourself, no bed is going to make all the pain go away. But every little bit can help.Let me get onto a couple other features that make this adjustable frame a standout in the industry. My wife loses her remote controls all the time. It is amazing how a person can be in bed and lose the remote. If you sleep with someone who has to call their cell phone to find it then the remote locate feature on this bed is worth a little extra money. Maybe someday I'll even lose the remote, and if so then this thing will be worth even more. ;-)The snore feature is pretty decent. It allows you to adjust your partner's side of the bed when they are snoring. My wife and I joked that we would have a snore-war after we got this bed, figuring we'd be busy using it on each other all night. The reality is that I've only used it a few times, and usually only when I'm watching TV after my wife has gone to sleep. It moves the bed just enough to get the person to shift, without actually waking them, and that is enough to stop (or at least soften) the snoring. She has reportedly used it on me a couple times as well, though I don't recall being roused that much while I am asleep. So I'd say this feature is a plus, so long as you don't abuse it.The programmable positions are also a great feature. We each control our own settings, which means that we each get a programmed position that fits us individually. There are four positions that you can set. I use setting 1 for the primary sleep position, setting w when working on the computer, 3 for TV, and 4for just relaxing or taking a quick nap. These positions allow me to quickly position the bed, and if they are not perfect for that moment then it also allows me to adjust from the position without having to do it all manually. In most instances, I use settings 2, 3 or 4 for typical nights, but sometimes I have to make just a little slight adjustment from time to time. The quick select program position allows me to get to the most used position and then go from there as my need changes. Frankly, I'm not sure you'd need more than 4 preset positions, but I guess someone might. The great thing is that I get to decide what my preset positions will be, not someone at the factory.The Sleep Timer is also pretty cool. My wife likes to fall asleep watching TV, so this feature is a great addition. She can set it for 30 or 60 minutes, and then when the timer goes off the bed moves to the primary position (usually the sleep position for most folks). I've also used this feature a couple times, and I can see how someone might get into a position where they'd use it all the time. I know the couple times I have used it I didn't really notice that I'd fallen asleep until the bed started moving. I had set my TV timer as well, so when the bed did move the TV was already off. It was actually as easy to do it this way than it was to turn the TV off, adjust everything, and then try to go to sleep. By being in the adjusted position I was already pretty comfortable, and that probably helps you to fall asleep faster anyway.Back to the massage feature for a moment. If you're like me, you probably remember the "Magic Fingers" massage beds in some hotels during the 60s and 70s. As a kid I thought those gizmos were great, but later in life I began to associate them with "cheap motels" rather than a quality sleeping experience.I also figured the massage system could be duplicated by sticking a cheap vibrator (the therapy kind, not the other) under the mattress. The problem with this thinking is that it is both more dangerous and a lot less convenient. Simply put, you'd have to shove at least 3 vibration sources under the mattress to even start to get close to what these systems do. And then you would not get the sleep timer or the alarm system.The massage itself is actually fairly good. You can set head and foot separately, which makes the overall system pretty nice for someone that has different needs at top and toe. I also like that the "wave" function moves the vibration up and down, according to how you set it.Let's wrap this up with some fiscal analysis. If you're in need of an adjustable frame, or you just want one, then the L&P models seems to be good choices. Once you make that plunge then you're in for at least $700 for a decent system from a reputable manufacturer. I won't even address the less expensive versions that are out there, let's just say that when it comes to your sleep comfort you do pretty much get what you pay for. With that said, the issue is really one of whether you chose to afford this setup. The difference in price between the S-cape and Prodigy was less than $200, and in the long run it was well worth it. The warranty is long enough to make you feel good about buying this product (and L&P has been around long enough you know they are probably going to be there if/when something goes wrong). So I figured that over the conservative estimate of the life of this system (probably 10 to 12 years) I would be spending less than $20/year ... or about $.05 a night for this kind of system. Well worth the investment, to me at least. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? column7: Customer Reviews Natural Latex Pillows Dual Zone Premium New - 2 Pack with Organic Covering - King Size 1 Review 5 star: (1)4 star: (0)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 5.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 5.0 out of 5 stars Highest Quality Latex Foam Pillow, May 11, 2012 By Ms. Rena Sproston "rena2007" (Wake Forest, NC) - See all my reviews(REAL NAME) Amazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Natural Latex Pillows Dual Zone Premium New - 2 Pack with Organic Covering - King Size These pillows are made of real organic latex, which is far superior to plastic memory foam products. Only real latex is a natural product compared to other foams. These pillows offer non-allergenic long term resiliency. These pillows (2 to a shipment) are of top quality, one piece (not shredded), and thick enough to offer good support. I would describe these as firm; however, firmness is very subjective. The 2 zones is an option that allows for more firmness in the neck region and a bit lesser firmness where your head lies, resulting in superior neck support; however, the company may offer other options. The pillows have a washable removable zippered cotton case. Before I discovered Organic Textiles, I searched for foam pillows, only to be disappointed in the plastic memory foam or lower priced thinner latex foam pillows. Now there is a high quality foam pillow available. True to size and of uncompromising quality, these pillows are highly recommended. I recommend this product and also the seller for excellent and friendly customer service. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? This review is from: Ma Maison Cordelia 500-Thread Count 6-Piece King Sheet Set, Blush (Kitchen) These feel soft to touch but wrinkle like crazy! I realize this is cheap price for 500ct 6pieces king size but they wrinkle so bad its not worth it to me cause it makes my bed look bad. I mean am i supposed to add starch to the wash or iron before folding or putting on the bed(like my grandmother did in the old days)? Bottom line is i have gotten better quality for a lil less, If you have patience to shop for deal then find cheaper sheet set or if you must have high quality then pay higher price, either way dont waste your money on these. column7: Customer Reviews 1000-Thread-Count Egyptian Cotton 1000TC Sheet Set, King, Brown Solid 1000 TC 1 Review 5 star: (1)4 star: (0)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 5.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 3 of 4 people found the following review helpful 5.0 out of 5 stars Great sheets!, November 11, 2008 By archimedes1 (San Ramon, CA United States) - See all my reviewsThis review is from: 1000-Thread-Count Egyptian Cotton 1000TC Sheet Set, King, Brown Solid 1000 TC We purchased two sheet sets from this vendor - both 1000TC, one set gold damask stripe, the other solid brown. Both sets are outstanding. The fabric is really nice. It's a fairly thick heavy cotton - it's actually comparable to flannel, but without the sticky furry feel. The fabric is soft but crisp. It washes just fine in the washer. There is elastic all the way around on the fitted sheet.The gold is a very warm color - on the orangy side. The brown is best described as pastel brown - sort of a chocolate mousse or latte color. It's very pretty. We are very happy with both sets of sheets. This review is from: Night Therapy 11" Euro Box Top Memory Foam and Pocketed Spring Hybrid Mattress Complete Set - King what a great product. I sleep well on it although I have the feeling that I have not put things together like they should be. Probably because information about this product is confusing and incomplete. I thought I was getting a "complete set." It turns out that I got a mattress but I do not know if this mattress is the "Complete set." Of course I sent the manufacturer of this great product an email and asked for clarification. The reply I got was that the order was filled on such and such date. Great! What about my question? So, I remain uncertain if I really got what I thought I was getting or whether I am sleeping comfortably on a falsely assembled bed. Is something missing? I guess I will never know, because the manufacturer never answered my question about the product. Have a great day! Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? column7: Customer Reviews 6pc King Size Hotel bedding set Including 300 Thread Count Duvet cover set Black with White+ king Down Alternative comforter 100% egyptian cotton by sheetsnthings 1 Review 5 star: (0)4 star: (1)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 4.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 4.0 out of 5 stars gorgeous bedding, February 1, 2011 By NCmomof4 (NC) - See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: 6pc King Size Hotel bedding set Including 300 Thread Count Duvet cover set Black with White+ king Down Alternative comforter 100% egyptian cotton by sheetsnthings (Kitchen) I bought this bedding to celebrate my new life, and I LOVE it. It's incredibly soft. The color is a lovely baby pink and rich chocolate brown, so sweet together. Every night when I go to bed I surround myself in the thick cloud of pink and drift off.I only have one complaint, and that's the size. I bought the king to put on my queen bed so it would be huge, and it isn't. It fits, but it barely covers the mattress completely, so it's definately NOT huge. The shams were a pain to put on my standard pillows too! So it could stand to be a bit bigger but otherwise, it's perfect. column7: Customer Reviews 1200 Thread Count King 4pc Bed Sheet Set 100% Egyptian Cotton Deep Pocket 1200 TC Solid Navy Blue 1 Review 5 star: (1)4 star: (0)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 5.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 4 of 4 people found the following review helpful 5.0 out of 5 stars Warm, soft, and wonderful, January 24, 2010 By F. Fleming - See all my reviews(REAL NAME) This review is from: 1200 Thread Count King 4pc Bed Sheet Set 100% Egyptian Cotton Deep Pocket 1200 TC Solid Navy Blue (Kitchen) I actually ordered the 600 TC bamboo/cotton blend sheets, but these are what I received. Disappointed that I wouldn't get to experience bamboo sheets (but elated that my TC had doubled), I washed the sheets in cold water and slapped them on my bed. Absolute bliss. These sheets are the softest sheets I've ever felt. They're also much warmer than my old sheets when they need to be. That is, they trap air and warmth wonderfully in the winter, but aren't too hot in the summer (I live in southern California, don't have air conditioning, and rarely use the heater). The sheets are deep enough that my thick mattress and memory foam fit comfortably. All in all, these sheets are great and I'm planning on buying another set soon. column7: Customer Reviews Stripes Lilac 300 Thread Count King size Sheet Set 100 % Egyptian Cotton 4pc Bed Sheet set (Deep Pocket) By sheetsnthings 1 Review 5 star: (1)4 star: (0)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 5.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 4 of 4 people found the following review helpful 5.0 out of 5 stars Lovely color, nice hand, washes well, May 11, 2011 By Nightingale (USA) - See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Stripes Lilac 300 Thread Count King size Sheet Set 100 % Egyptian Cotton 4pc Bed Sheet set (Deep Pocket) By sheetsnthings Stripes Lilac 300 Thread Count King size Sheet Set 100 % Egyptian Cotton 4pc Bed Sheet set (Deep Pocket) By sheetsnthingsI bought this set to replace a set I ordered by mistake -- my mistake, not the seller's: I ordered California King Size rather than regular King Size. The original return was accepted quickly and my refund processed promptly. I was in a hurry and didn't double-check my order which was clearly marked as to size. I did have to pay return shipping, but since it was my fault, I can't complain. I will not hesitate to use sheetsnthings again, they have treated me well in several transactions and they have provided quality bedding at a good price and shipped promptly.When I received the new set of sheets (in the right size), I immediately washed them and put them on the bed. They handled washing very well without shrinking or discoloring. I wash all sheets before I use them in HOT water and dry on HIGH HEAT setting because of dust/dust mite allergies, so if they won't handle that treatment, I don't use them and any defects in the fabric or the sewing tend to become apparent right away. The sheets seem soft enough for 300 thread count and do not seem to be prone to excessive wrinkling. While they are not overly soft, the fabric does seem to soften a bit more with each washing. After 2 (very rough) washings, I have not seen any pilling or holes, no shrinking at all, and a good even texture overall. The listing states that they are 100% Egyptian Cotton (long staple) and I can see no reason not to accept that claim. I have no complaints what-so-ever about the quality of the product or the processing of my order. I am well-pleased with this purchase.A note about color: These sheets are a soft, deep lavender (not an Easter-egg-bright color) and when I first saw them in the package they almost seemed to be a beige/taupe color. But after putting them on the bed the color is better appreciated; it is a rich lavender shade that has a "quality" look to it. The color held up after washing and adds a soft, rich effect to my bedding. The color is a true lavender with an earthy mink-like undertone, not a bright, splashy, tint of lavender if that is what you're looking for. The woven in stripe adds a nice touch as well. (New Jersey) - See all my reviews(REAL NAME) This review is from: Jim Shore Heartwood Creek Three Kings Revolving Musical Figurine, 10-3/4-Inch (Kitchen) Our family celebrates Three Kings Day (a.k.a. Epiphany) and I wanted to have some beautiful pieces to decorate our home with in honor of the three magi. This figurine is stunning! I love Jim Shore and I have many pieces in my collection, but this one is, by far, my favorite!The music is, appropriately, "We Three Kings of Orient Are". Really good., January 10, 2012 By Juan V. - See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Veratex 459078 Full size Dobby Stripe Sheet Set, Black (Kitchen) This 400 thread count sheet set is not just okay but actually good for a 40 bucks purchase. The fitted sheet won't slip, no matter how much you roll during the night, fabric is not thin/transluscent at all and color won't fade quickly or stain the mattress. This review is from: King/CalKing Comforter Set 100% Egyptian Cotton 550 Thread Count Duvet Cover Set + Comforter - Navy Blue I love this comforter. It's definitely large enough for my king-size bed. The duvet, itself, is probably a little wider than I need (it pretty much touches the floor- just like picture), since it's also supposed to be able to fit a cal-king bed as well.The comforter is light in weight, but does a great job of keeping me warm toasty. I don't think I'll have any problem getting in my washing machine if/when the time comes to wash it. The duvet cover is very soft. It was a little hard to get on (so many buttons), but that's probably par for the course.When all put together, the comforter, duvet, and pillow covers look, for the most part, just like the picture. The only difference is that the duvet is a very pretty shade of royal blue, which the picture doesn't quite capture. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? column7: Customer Reviews Bellino Fine Linens Mille Righe King Flat Sheets Set, Ivory 1 Review 5 star: (0)4 star: (1)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 4.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 4.0 out of 5 stars my first fine linen sheet set, April 26, 2012 By Guy M. Kitashiro "gkitash" (Honolulu, HI) - See all my reviews(REAL NAME) Amazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Bellino Fine Linens Mille Righe Queen Flat Sheets Set, Ivory (Kitchen) I got a set of Bellino Mille Righe sheets after staying at Caesars Palace and discovering that they use Anachini linens. The beds in the Forum Tower are very comfortable and luxurious. After finding that Anachini linens are about $750 a set, I looked around for similar linens that were less expensive. I decided on Bellino linens as they fit the requirements; fine linen made in Italy, Egyptian cotton, 300+ thread count, etc. I also purchased four Bellino Mille Righe pillow cases.After the first wash, I tried them and was hoping for the luxurious feel of Anachini linens used at Caesars. The Bellino linens felt nice, but they also felt slightly stiff. These linens were no where near $750 a set, but I didn't expect them to feel stiff. However, after washing them a second time, a lot of the stiffness seems to have been washed out of the sheets. I remember reading that linen gets softer with washing.I'm looking forward to using these sheets after the third washing. All in all, I still feel these linens are rather expensive (at 40% the cost of Anachini linens). But I'm also thinking that the Bellino linens are worth the expense due to the intangible dimension and feel they provide.
