column7: Customer Reviews Martex Brentwood Gold Label King Size Hotel Pillow Set (2 King Pillows) 1 Review 5 star: (0)4 star: (1)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 4.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 4.0 out of 5 stars One is not like the other!, October 30, 2011 By S. Flegel (Seattle, WA) - See all my reviews(REAL NAME) Amazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Martex Brentwood Gold Label King Size Hotel Pillow Set (2 King Pillows) The four stars is for the one good pillow of the two we received. The problem pillow, if it had been the only pillow received, would've received just one or two stars.We were looking forward to receiving this 2-pillow shipment, but once they arrived and gave them a try, it quickly became apparent that these pillows apparently are not consistently made, or at least, there is an occasional pillow not meeting the usual standards of which we were unlucky to get one. We're now hoping to be able to return one of the two pillows for a refund of half the purchase price, as we'd like to keep the other that seems OK. The wife LOVES the pillow, actually, saying that the frequent neck kinks she used to get with her old Tempur-Pedic have completely stopped. column7: Customer Reviews Harbor House Preston King Comforter Set 1 Review 5 star: (0)4 star: (1)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 4.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 4.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful!, May 30, 2012 By drsmith2002 - See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Harbor House Preston Queen Comforter Set (Misc.) I had been searching for a comforter set for our guest room and was pleased to have found this one! The colors are close to what the picture shows but the comforter has just a touch more grey in it than I thought it would. I was worried it would be too dark once on the bed but it wasn't. That said, it still looks great and I couldn't be happier. I accented the room with white curtains, flowers and lamp shades and it made the room feel nice and bright. The comforter fits the bed (I bought a queen) just fine. My only con on this comforter set is the comforter is not as thick as I would have liked but it works for a guest room where it won't be used every day. column7: Customer Reviews Sanders Home Collection Henna Reversible 10-Piece Bed in a Bag Bedding Set with Pillows, King Size, Teal 1 Review 5 star: (0)4 star: (0)3 star: (1)2 star: (0)1 star: (0) Average Customer Review 3.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 1 of 1 people found the following review helpful 3.0 out of 5 stars Slightly disappointed!, June 16, 2012 By Lola (Fort Wayne, IN United States) - See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Sanders Home Collection Henna Reversible 10-Piece Bed in a Bag Bedding Set with Pillows, Queen Size, Teal (Misc.) I needed a change in bedding to brighten up my bedroom. We all know how manufacturers love to make their cheaper bedding products so much uglier than their more expensive ones. From the picture, this bedding set looked perfect for the colors in my room. Well, it's not as pictured. The blue is a bit darker than this picture displays. Even the picture on the packaging displays this same picture - only the product itself is darker and looks a bit cheaper up close. I suppose I should wash it several times and maybe the colors will calm down a bit. That being said, it still brightens up the room, but for some reason, just the simple change in the blue makes this product look more like a child's bedding set than for an adult. Also, while this is for a queen size bed, the comforter is a bit small. Funny, I almost bought the king size set but figured the sheets would be too big. I probably should send it back but it's almost not worth the hassle of trying to get everything back in the plastic wrapping.I'm a pretty frugal shopper and part of me is a bit disappointed in this comforter. But, when I break it down and think how much everything would cost separately, it's not so bad. Especially when considering all the super ugly patterns and colors that are out there in the affordable range.I'm repainting another bedroom and because it's reversible, this comforter will probably fit in nicer in that room once I'm finished, especially since that room has a full size bed and this will end up being perfect. So, in the long run, I'll end up being satisfied with this bedding set. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? Holmes (Auburn, NE) - See all my reviews(VINE VOICE) (REAL NAME) Amazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Sferra Brothers Kingston - King Blanket Mushroom I've never been a fan of great big fluffy comforters and prefer to layer blankets. I chose this one because it was oversized and would cover my deep mattress king sized bed and it does a great job. The material quality is great and even better I'm able to wash and dry it in a normal sized washer and dryer so no more trips to the laundromat to use the commercial machines.The blanket is warm enough though I don't really have a need for another one when I keep the temperature in my bedroom down around 64-65. Boston - See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Luxurious Full Size Zebra Print Satin Sheet Set I saw many zebra printed sets before selecting this one. column7: Customer Reviews Patina King Comforter Set, Gray 1 Review 5 star: (0)4 star: (0)3 star: (0)2 star: (0)1 star: (1) Average Customer Review 1.0 out of 5 stars (1 customer review) Share your thoughts with other customers Create your own review Search Customer Reviews Only search this product's reviews Most Helpful First | Newest First 1 of 1 people found the following review helpful 1.0 out of 5 stars Too Small/Color is off, March 8, 2012 By D.A. - See all my reviewsAmazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Patina King Comforter Set, Gray (Kitchen) This comforter is okay in quality as far as the stitching, but that is the only plus side. The king size does come close to covering a king bed. The color is blue-gray, but more blue than gray. The photo makes the cotton appear to be shiney and soft, but the "grey" looks tye-dyed and is quite dull. The fabric is not soft at all. Not sure if they are all like this, but mine will be going back. Help other customers find the most helpful reviews Was this review helpful to you? Adams "American Citizen" (Warroad, MN United States) - See all my reviews(REAL NAME) Amazon Verified Purchase(What's this?) This review is from: Eve Queen Quilt I certainly hope there were no poor schmucks out there who bought this thing for $250...even without fading! Yes, it is a 2nd and there is fading in the fabric. That's bad enough, but it's on the green (it's green...kind of avocado green rather than a sort of teal or aqua as it shows in the photos-not pretty) rather than the floral side. It's also hard and stiff...you have to kind of bend it...it's not soft and comfy...and it smells like petroleum or something. To add insult to injury, I paid to have this thing shipped to me and will have to pay again to ship it back. At least $20 down the drain. Some bargain. Very disappointing.
